tor organized a symposium at McGill University to discuss the possibilities of preparing such an index. The resulting papers by six symposium participants— Barbara Becker-Cantarino, Peter M. Daly, Peter Erb, G. Richard Dimler, Lorelei Robins, and Alan Young—contribute to our knowledge of the emblems of Peacham and Corrozet, the Dutch love emblems, the Jesuit emblem, and emblems used in books of mediation. The essays also discuss the problems and procedures involved in preparing an Index Emblematicus, a work which would serve scholars working in the fields of literature, art, culture, religion, history, and the languages. The volume is richly illustrated with over forty emblem reproductions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEmblem booksxAbstracting and indexing. 0aEmblemsxThemes, motivesxEurope. 0aEmblemszEuropexThemes, motives. 0aEmblèmesxThèmes, motifsxEuropexEuropa. 0aLivres à figuresxAnalyse et indexation des documents. 4aArt. 4aReligion. 7aART / European.2bisacsh1 aBecker-Cantarino, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaly, Peter M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDimler, G. Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErb, Peter C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobins, Lorelei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Alan R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920844540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889208445423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.c